1:03:29.413 --> 1:03:30.965
Goodnight, dad.

1:03:31.000 --> 1:03:33.000
Love you more than ice cream.

1:03:33.068 --> 1:03:35.827
Love you more than cake.

1:03:35.896 --> 1:03:38.896
Love you more
than ice cream cake.

1:03:38.931 --> 1:03:40.137
That's not your thing.

1:03:40.172 --> 1:03:41.965
You're makin' that up.

1:03:42.000 --> 1:03:43.241
Yeah, it's time for bed.

1:03:43.275 --> 1:03:44.413
We can go to the fair tomorrow,
okay?

1:03:44.448 --> 1:03:45.448
Okay.

1:03:45.482 --> 1:03:47.275
- Goodnight.
- Night light.

1:03:47.275 --> 1:03:48.793
Yeah, I'll put it on right now.

1:03:52.000 --> 1:03:53.172
JAMES:
Dad.

1:03:53.241 --> 1:03:55.103
Yeah?

1:03:55.137 --> 1:03:57.896
JAMES:
We're not going to Disneyland,
are we?

1:04:00.620 --> 1:04:04.379
Yes, we are, I promise.

1:04:04.413 --> 1:04:07.206
JAMES:
It's okay
you can't afford it, dad.

1:04:09.172 --> 1:04:11.517
James.

1:04:11.551 --> 1:04:13.379
Son, look at me.

1:04:15.241 --> 1:04:18.344
We're going to Disneyland.

1:04:18.379 --> 1:04:20.965
I promise.

1:04:21.000 --> 1:04:24.965
We just have to save up
for it first.

1:04:25.000 --> 1:04:27.655
Every penny matters.

1:04:27.655 --> 1:04:28.896
That's right, son.

1:04:33.172 --> 1:04:35.310
Did you take the money, daddy?

1:04:41.172 --> 1:04:42.344
Go to bed.

1:04:49.517 --> 1:04:51.068
I don't know, I want 'em all.

1:04:51.137 --> 1:04:52.551
Well, you better get
what you can

1:04:52.586 --> 1:04:54.689
while you got a chance
before the laws change,

1:04:54.724 --> 1:04:56.965
'cause it's really only
a matter of time.

1:04:57.000 --> 1:04:58.344
Hey.

1:04:58.344 --> 1:05:00.241
Hey, Mr. Bill, how you doin'
this fine evenin'?

1:05:00.310 --> 1:05:01.344
Yeah, yeah.

1:05:03.241 --> 1:05:03.724
Fine.

1:05:03.758 --> 1:05:05.241
What's all this?

1:05:05.275 --> 1:05:08.413
WINSLOW:
This is my fine selection
of firearms.

1:05:08.448 --> 1:05:10.206
We're gonna be shootin'
these on Sunday.

1:05:10.241 --> 1:05:11.482
Like I said before,
it'd be really cool

1:05:11.551 --> 1:05:12.689
if you could join us.

1:05:12.724 --> 1:05:14.724
We will have a good time.

1:05:14.758 --> 1:05:17.206
- Are these things loaded?
- LIAM: No, no.

1:05:17.241 --> 1:05:18.275
Because my son is right there

1:05:18.344 --> 1:05:19.724
and I really don't feel
comfortable with you guys

1:05:19.758 --> 1:05:20.965
having these in the house

1:05:21.034 --> 1:05:22.241
- and I'm--
- LIAM: No, no.

1:05:22.275 --> 1:05:25.655
Only gun I ever carry loaded
is right here in my holster.

1:05:25.724 --> 1:05:27.448
You guys are shooting
all of these on Sunday?

1:05:28.448 --> 1:05:30.275
Yes, sir, we are.

1:05:30.310 --> 1:05:31.965
Every damn one of 'em.

1:05:32.034 --> 1:05:34.310
- You should come.
- No, I can't.

1:05:34.379 --> 1:05:36.620
Well, I'm buyin'
the assault rifle on Friday.

1:05:36.655 --> 1:05:38.103
I think it'd be good to have
a firearm around

1:05:38.137 --> 1:05:39.517
for the protection, you know?

1:05:39.551 --> 1:05:41.241
For home protection?

1:05:41.275 --> 1:05:43.241
You need one of these
for home protection?

1:05:43.275 --> 1:05:44.758
From what, a bear?

1:05:44.758 --> 1:05:47.379
We do live in uncertain times,
Mr. Bell.

1:05:47.413 --> 1:05:49.965
Liam, my son is right there.

1:05:50.034 --> 1:05:51.034
I don't feel comfortable
with you

1:05:51.068 --> 1:05:53.482
having this in the house.

1:05:53.551 --> 1:05:56.379
I'm also buyin' a trigger lock
and a locking gun case.

1:06:02.275 --> 1:06:06.517
WINSLOW:
Safe as rain, Mr. Bell,
I guaran-damn-tee it.

1:06:06.551 --> 1:06:08.310
Hey, I'm gonna step out
for a smoke.

1:06:08.344 --> 1:06:10.241
You guys cool?

1:06:10.275 --> 1:06:11.413
Yeah.

1:06:11.448 --> 1:06:13.103
Awesome.

1:06:17.655 --> 1:06:20.655
So you buy and sell
these things?

1:06:20.655 --> 1:06:23.517
I mean you got a shitload
of guns.

1:06:23.551 --> 1:06:26.482
You interested in purchasin'
a firearm or sellin' them,

1:06:26.482 --> 1:06:30.103
- for that matter.
- No, no.

1:06:30.137 --> 1:06:31.172
Well--

1:06:33.103 --> 1:06:36.137
It's my card, as they say.

1:06:36.172 --> 1:06:38.827
Got all my complete
contact information on there.

1:06:38.827 --> 1:06:40.482
All that pertinent information
is located right there

1:06:40.482 --> 1:06:42.655
in front of the card.

1:06:42.689 --> 1:06:44.827
And on the back of the card.

1:06:44.862 --> 1:06:47.275
That there's a picture
of an M1 Abrams tank.

1:06:48.620 --> 1:06:49.793
I know.

1:06:52.379 --> 1:06:55.379
Give me a call if you change
your mind, Mr. Bell.

1:06:55.448 --> 1:06:58.344
I'd be here within the hour
with guns in hand.

1:06:58.379 --> 1:07:00.344
Or cash to buy
if you're sellin'.

1:07:00.344 --> 1:07:01.862
Okay.

1:07:01.896 --> 1:07:03.724
What about background checks?

1:07:05.551 --> 1:07:06.758
What about 'em?

1:07:11.896 --> 1:07:15.724
Hey, I also carry about
10 grand in cash

1:07:15.758 --> 1:07:20.034
at all times for that
more discreet customer.

1:07:23.241 --> 1:07:25.241
I do have some very important
business to discuss

1:07:25.275 --> 1:07:27.379
- with my compatriot Liam.
- Mmhmm.

1:07:27.379 --> 1:07:28.758
You'll excuse me Mr. Bell.

1:07:28.827 --> 1:07:30.413
I'll talk to you later.

1:07:30.448 --> 1:07:31.724
You got my card,
you can give a call

1:07:31.758 --> 1:07:33.344
if you change your mind.

1:07:33.379 --> 1:07:34.344
Okay.

1:08:41.551 --> 1:08:42.931
What do want to do, bud?

1:08:44.655 --> 1:08:45.758
Yeah.

1:08:52.655 --> 1:08:53.724
Oh, look at this one,
that's a goat.

1:08:53.758 --> 1:08:54.931
- Do you see him?
- Yeah.

1:08:54.931 --> 1:08:55.931
Yeah.

1:09:36.896 --> 1:09:40.517
"And Prince Ernest knew
what he must do.

1:09:40.551 --> 1:09:45.000
Climb to the top
of Midnight Mountain."

1:09:46.827 --> 1:09:48.689
That is it for tonight.

1:09:48.724 --> 1:09:50.689
- Time for bed, okay?
- Okay.

1:09:50.724 --> 1:09:52.827
Here, lay down
and get all covered up.

1:09:52.827 --> 1:09:55.000
Alright, got your dinosaur.

1:09:55.000 --> 1:09:56.620
- Good?
- Yeah.

1:09:56.655 --> 1:09:57.655
Alright.

1:10:01.482 --> 1:10:02.793
Love you, buddy.

1:10:02.827 --> 1:10:04.241
Goodnight, dad.

1:10:04.310 --> 1:10:05.551
Love you.

1:10:05.586 --> 1:10:07.827
Love you more than ice cream.

1:10:07.862 --> 1:10:10.724
More than birthday cake
ice cream?

1:10:10.793 --> 1:10:11.724
Yeah.

1:10:13.793 --> 1:10:14.862
Alright, goodnight,
go to sleep.

1:11:03.068 --> 1:11:04.068
Get your backpack, James.

1:11:04.068 --> 1:11:05.586
Don't leave it out here.

1:11:05.586 --> 1:11:07.724
Go on inside
and put it your room.

1:11:07.724 --> 1:11:08.931
- Hey.
- Hey.

1:11:08.931 --> 1:11:10.551
Did you guys have
a good weekend?

1:11:10.551 --> 1:11:11.413
Yeah.

1:11:11.448 --> 1:11:14.310
Good, I'm glad.

1:11:14.379 --> 1:11:15.758
Sorry, we're late.

1:11:15.793 --> 1:11:16.896
That's okay.

1:11:16.931 --> 1:11:18.413
It's--

1:11:18.448 --> 1:11:22.517
- Is my mom still here?
- No.

1:11:22.551 --> 1:11:25.551
What was she doing here?

1:11:25.586 --> 1:11:27.310
She was helping me pack.

1:11:27.379 --> 1:11:29.724
Pack, for what?

1:11:30.655 --> 1:11:32.689
Come on inside, Grey,
we need to talk.

1:11:35.689 --> 1:11:37.931
Grey, close the door.

1:11:37.965 --> 1:11:39.206
James, go to your room, honey.

1:11:39.241 --> 1:11:41.896
Mommy wants to talk to daddy
in private for a minute, okay?

1:11:48.068 --> 1:11:51.724
So what's going on?

1:11:53.413 --> 1:11:55.862
- We're moving, Grey.
- Oh, okay.

1:11:55.896 --> 1:12:00.586
Um, you need my help
moving stuff or--

1:12:02.482 --> 1:12:04.724
It's California.

1:12:04.793 --> 1:12:09.517
My job had a management opening
in San Pedro, I applied,

1:12:09.551 --> 1:12:14.000
I was a perfect candidate,
and I got the job.

1:12:14.034 --> 1:12:17.620
Okay, it's a good job,
it's a huge salary increase,

1:12:17.655 --> 1:12:20.620
and they'll help pay for us
to relocate.

1:12:20.655 --> 1:12:22.827
I can finally take James
to Disneyland.

1:12:22.827 --> 1:12:24.758
I was gonna take James
to Disneyland.

1:12:24.793 --> 1:12:27.000
No, you weren't, Grey.

1:12:27.000 --> 1:12:29.689
You've been stringing him along
for two years now.

1:12:29.758 --> 1:12:31.965
Putting pennies in a jar?

1:12:32.000 --> 1:12:34.379
Are you for real?

1:12:34.448 --> 1:12:35.655
He knows you're broke, Grey.

1:12:35.655 --> 1:12:37.620
He's not stupid, okay?
He knows.

1:12:37.655 --> 1:12:38.689
I'm looking for another job.

1:12:38.758 --> 1:12:40.586
Stop it, okay?

1:12:40.620 --> 1:12:42.103
Just stop!

1:12:42.137 --> 1:12:44.379
You're not looking
for a better job,

1:12:44.448 --> 1:12:46.862
you're not taking him
to Disneyland.

1:12:46.896 --> 1:12:51.000
You're breaking his heart
and he loves you.

1:12:51.034 --> 1:12:53.517
Okay, I don't wanna fight
about this anymore.

1:12:53.551 --> 1:12:54.896
We're workin'
on our book together.

1:12:54.965 --> 1:12:56.793
As soon as it's done,
then we're gonna sell it,

1:12:56.827 --> 1:12:57.827
- and I'm gonna--
- Your book?

1:12:57.862 --> 1:13:00.379
- Your-- your stupid ogre book?
- Yes, our--

1:13:00.448 --> 1:13:01.689
The one that you
you've been working on

1:13:01.689 --> 1:13:03.000
- since he was born?
- Yeah--

1:13:03.034 --> 1:13:04.000
- That book?
- Yes, that book.

1:13:04.034 --> 1:13:05.103
We're workin' on it together--

1:13:05.172 --> 1:13:06.793
And as soon as it's finished,
we're gonna sell it.

1:13:06.862 --> 1:13:10.827
Grey, just stop and listen
to yourself, okay?

1:13:10.862 --> 1:13:13.689
I can't wait for you anymore.

1:13:20.586 --> 1:13:26.034
Grey, I have waited for you
for almost two years.

1:13:26.068 --> 1:13:30.517
I have sat here day after day
and night after night,

1:13:30.551 --> 1:13:32.620
watching you break
our son's heart

1:13:32.689 --> 1:13:35.448
by being a failure
who can't even afford

1:13:35.517 --> 1:13:38.068
to take care of his family.

1:13:38.103 --> 1:13:39.206
Look at you!

1:13:39.206 --> 1:13:42.068
You can't even take care
of yourself!

1:13:42.103 --> 1:13:45.034
And I've given up on you, Grey.

1:13:45.068 --> 1:13:49.793
I have finally realized that
this is who you are.

1:13:49.862 --> 1:13:53.689
I am sorry, but we are moving
and we're never coming back.

1:13:53.724 --> 1:13:55.517
I told you that I'm lookin'
for another job.

1:13:56.517 --> 1:13:59.137
I'm gonna figure something out,
okay?

1:13:59.206 --> 1:14:01.103
I can start paying more towards
his daycare if that helps.

1:14:01.137 --> 1:14:04.000
It's too late, Grey.

1:14:04.068 --> 1:14:07.655
Are you taking your meds?

1:14:07.724 --> 1:14:11.000
No, I-- I can't afford 'em.

1:14:11.068 --> 1:14:13.241
You can't afford them?

1:14:13.275 --> 1:14:16.137
Tell me, Grey,
what can you afford, huh?

1:14:16.172 --> 1:14:20.896
What can Mr. Greyson Bell,
fabulous artist, afford?

1:14:20.931 --> 1:14:21.965
I'll be fine.

1:14:22.034 --> 1:14:24.620
I just have to make it
through a couple of weeks.

1:14:24.655 --> 1:14:26.000
MARILYN:
A couple of weeks?

1:14:26.068 --> 1:14:28.103
Didn't you say
a couple of weeks last week?

1:14:28.137 --> 1:14:30.103
And this week,
and then next paycheck,

1:14:30.137 --> 1:14:31.482
and next month?

1:14:31.551 --> 1:14:33.103
What about now?

1:14:33.103 --> 1:14:35.172
I'll start paying child support.

1:14:35.241 --> 1:14:37.793
- Is that what you want?
- I don't want child support!

1:14:37.793 --> 1:14:40.586
I don't want anything from you,
I never have.

1:14:40.620 --> 1:14:45.586
All I wanted was you
to be a man, and a father,

1:14:45.620 --> 1:14:48.724
and to provide for his son!

1:14:48.758 --> 1:14:50.620
MARILYN:
I wanted you.

1:14:58.586 --> 1:15:00.793
I'm trying.

1:15:00.827 --> 1:15:02.551
No, you're not!

1:15:02.620 --> 1:15:03.965
Don't you dare say that!

1:15:04.000 --> 1:15:06.689
I don't you dare put this on me!

1:15:06.689 --> 1:15:08.655
MARILYN:
This is on you, Grey, you!

1:15:11.034 --> 1:15:15.310
This is who you are, this is all
you'll ever amount to.

1:15:15.344 --> 1:15:16.827
Are you happy?

1:15:16.827 --> 1:15:18.896
Are you fuckin' happy?

1:15:18.965 --> 1:15:20.827
Okay, I said it.

1:15:20.827 --> 1:15:23.000
- I can't--
- No.

1:15:23.000 --> 1:15:25.344
Yeah, well, neither am I.

1:15:31.206 --> 1:15:33.827
Why are you looking
at your phone?

1:15:33.862 --> 1:15:35.206
It's not like you've paid
your bill in months,

1:15:35.241 --> 1:15:38.172
you don't even have service!

1:15:38.172 --> 1:15:42.172
This is exactly the kind of shit
that I'm talking about!

1:15:42.206 --> 1:15:45.137
You can't just go on pretending
everything's okay

1:15:45.172 --> 1:15:47.000
like nobody notices.

1:15:53.689 --> 1:15:54.896
Please.

1:15:59.862 --> 1:16:03.724
Please, don't take my son away.

1:16:03.758 --> 1:16:05.620
Please, he's the only good thing

1:16:05.689 --> 1:16:09.068
I have left in my life, please.

1:16:09.068 --> 1:16:10.379
Please, don't take him away.

1:16:10.413 --> 1:16:12.965
No, we're moving to California,
you can come visit him there.

1:16:13.034 --> 1:16:14.413
I can't afford that.

1:16:14.413 --> 1:16:16.137
Then get a better job!

1:16:16.206 --> 1:16:18.310
I'll get an attorney.

1:16:18.379 --> 1:16:20.103
You can't even afford
to feed your son

1:16:20.137 --> 1:16:23.034
and you're threatening me
with an attorney!

1:16:23.068 --> 1:16:25.068
Go to hell, Grey!

1:16:25.103 --> 1:16:26.896
He deserves a better father
than you.

1:16:26.896 --> 1:16:27.862
Don't say that!

1:16:33.068 --> 1:16:36.896
JAMES:
Daddy, stop, don't hurt mommy.

1:16:36.931 --> 1:16:38.413
MARILYN:
Grey, please go away.

1:16:38.448 --> 1:16:41.137
Don't ever, ever come back.

1:16:41.206 --> 1:16:42.724
Just go.

1:16:44.103 --> 1:16:46.034
Go!

1:16:55.275 --> 1:16:56.896
GREYSON:
Yes, I understand that
it's closed on the weekend,

1:16:56.931 --> 1:16:58.206
but this is an emergency.

1:17:01.103 --> 1:17:03.827
Yes.

1:17:03.862 --> 1:17:05.103
Well, how much would that cost?

1:17:09.275 --> 1:17:10.965
Wait--

1:17:11.000 --> 1:17:13.793
It costs how much to--
to file in court on Monday?

1:17:21.034 --> 1:17:22.068
No, I--

1:17:26.310 --> 1:17:28.103
No, I don't have any money.

1:17:31.137 --> 1:17:34.310
I don't know what else to do,
please, I need help.

1:17:40.379 --> 1:17:42.103
She's gonna take my son.

1:20:08.344 --> 1:20:10.275
Hey, Mr. Bell.

1:20:10.275 --> 1:20:13.344
How you doin' this fine evenin'?

1:20:13.413 --> 1:20:16.448
Where's my partner in crime?

1:20:16.448 --> 1:20:17.965
My dear friend and colleague
Mr. Brady,

1:20:18.000 --> 1:20:20.448
where's he at tonight?

1:20:20.448 --> 1:20:22.965
Oh man, we had a hell
of a time shootin' today.

1:20:23.000 --> 1:20:25.931
It's a damn shame
you couldn't make it.

1:20:25.931 --> 1:20:28.275
He's with Janice.

1:20:28.275 --> 1:20:29.310
WINSLOW:
No shit.

1:20:30.206 --> 1:20:33.275
Well, he is quite
the ladies' man.

1:20:33.275 --> 1:20:35.931
As I'm sure you are, too,
Mr. Bell,

1:20:35.931 --> 1:20:37.241
speakin' of the ladies.

1:20:40.068 --> 1:20:41.103
You can almost fit
this little bastard

1:20:41.103 --> 1:20:42.103
in your boot.

1:20:44.482 --> 1:20:47.448
Check that out.

1:20:47.448 --> 1:20:49.068
That's pretty good convenient.

1:20:49.103 --> 1:20:50.413
Hmm.

1:20:52.413 --> 1:20:54.586
What about one like yours?

1:20:54.620 --> 1:20:57.344
My 9 mil?

1:20:57.413 --> 1:21:01.068
It's got some decent
stoppin' power in this one.

1:21:01.137 --> 1:21:02.413
I got a couple in my selection
right now

1:21:02.482 --> 1:21:04.482
if you're interested.

1:21:04.482 --> 1:21:06.482
Can I see it?

1:21:06.482 --> 1:21:07.551
Have a hand at it.

1:21:11.379 --> 1:21:15.241
Use two hands,
you'd be more accurate.

1:21:15.310 --> 1:21:16.275
There you go.

1:21:16.344 --> 1:21:21.000
Wanna close that left eye,
sight that sucker.

1:21:21.034 --> 1:21:22.068
Uh-huh.

1:21:22.137 --> 1:21:23.482
That's what I'm talkin' about.

1:21:27.206 --> 1:21:29.689
Do you have more bullets
for these?

1:21:29.689 --> 1:21:32.034
WINSLOW:
Hell yeah, I got some out
in my truck right now.

1:21:32.068 --> 1:21:35.413
I can get you some ammo
for that HK.

1:21:35.482 --> 1:21:37.068
Enough rounds for that bad boy
to take you

1:21:37.137 --> 1:21:41.068
right through the apocalypse,
reliable.

1:21:41.137 --> 1:21:44.931
Cash is okay?

1:21:45.000 --> 1:21:48.344
WINSLOW:
Cash is legal currency,
Mr. Bell.

1:21:48.379 --> 1:21:51.344
Okay.

1:21:51.379 --> 1:21:54.689
I want one like this,
and some bullets for it,

1:21:54.724 --> 1:21:57.482
and bullets for the--
the one that Liam got.

1:21:59.172 --> 1:22:00.448
We're going shooting.

1:22:00.517 --> 1:22:02.965
No shit!

1:22:03.034 --> 1:22:05.310
Well, fuck it, hey.

1:22:05.379 --> 1:22:07.068
I'll go get some ammo
